    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@company.com"
  },
  "recipients": [
    "authorized.recipient@company.com",
    "security@company.com",
    "ceo@company.com"
  ],
  "subject": "URGENT: Suspected Breach of Sensitive Employee Data - Immediate Action Required",
  "body": "EMAIL NOTICE - Privileged and Confidential; Subject to Non-Disclosure\n\nWe have become aware of a suspected breach of sensitive employee data belonging to [Company Name]. This may include personal information, Social Security numbers, and other confidential data.\n\nTo contain the potential breach and mitigate any risks, we require your immediate cooperation:\n\n- Cease and desist: Stop all review, use, disclosure, and dissemination of the data. Do not attempt to access or share it further.\n- Identify scope: Provide a written list of all individuals, systems, and third parties that may have received or accessed the data, including dates/times, storage locations, and onward transfers.\n- Preserve evidence: Implement an immediate litigation hold. Preserve logs, devices, emails, messaging, collaboration platforms, cloud storage, and backups reflecting any potential access or dissemination. Do not alter, wipe, or forensically clean any systems.\n- Secure the data: Segregate and securely return any copies of the data via the link provided. Do not transmit via ordinary email or unsecured channels.\n- Certify deletion: For any copies inadvertently stored on your systems, place them in legal hold, and coordinate with us for verified deletion. Provide a signed Certification of Deletion and Non-Use.\n\nYour timely cooperation is critical to enable accurate scoping and mitigation. Please send your written confirmation of the above items to legal@[company].com within 24 hours.\n\nReservation of rights: We reserve the right to seek all appropriate legal remedies, including injunctive relief, damages, and fees.",
